cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.CY 

This paper deals with privacy-preserving data analysis, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is "cs.CR" (Cryptography and Security) since the paper proposes a new framework for local differential privacy. The paper also provides information-theoretic lower bounds, which suggests that it could belong to "cs.IT" (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper proposes sample-optimal schemes for discrete distribution estimation, which could place it under "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with data management and privacy, which could place it under "cs.DB" (Databases). Finally, the paper discusses geolocation and web search applications, which could place it under "cs.CY" (Computers and Society).
